00:09:15.944 --> 00:09:20.655
Just assign your starting point
as zero zero, like the origin on

00:09:20.655 --> 00:09:25.814
a graph movements to the east will
increase your X coordinate because

00:09:25.935 --> 00:09:27.704
you are moving right on the graph.

00:09:28.120 --> 00:09:31.420
Movements to the west will
decrease your X coordinate.

00:09:31.540 --> 00:09:36.189
Moving left movements to the north
will increase your Y coordinate.

00:09:36.339 --> 00:09:40.870
Going up and movements to the south
will decrease your Y coordinate.

00:09:40.990 --> 00:09:46.750
Going down your final coordinates
XY will then effortlessly help you

00:09:46.750 --> 00:09:51.430
