EastWest axis sum up all eastward

00:10:19.495 --> 00:10:23.395
movements as positive and all
westward movements as negative.

00:10:23.785 --> 00:10:26.305
This gives you your net EW displacement.

00:10:26.939 --> 00:10:31.860
These two net displacement north,
south, and east west will conveniently

00:10:31.860 --> 00:10:36.480
form the two perpendicular sides of a
right angle triangle, allowing you to

00:10:36.540 --> 00:10:38.699
quickly calculate the shortest distance.

